Polished **`src/blog/people/drafts/julia-fox.md`**.

## What I found
This draft was already in strong shape — it had been through a fresh-eyes review and a full second pass, and its emotional layer was intact (the empty-fridge interior beat, the Kanye "chosen" empathy turn, and the Gianna grief thread that Fox "could never turn into art"). So this was a genuine light-touch pass, not a rescue.

## What I cleaned up
The only real problem was **one strong contrast-pair engine** the second pass had missed (its ledger claimed 0, but the report found 1):

- **L146:** `"Not luck, not a stylist."` → `"No stylist built them; she did, from whatever was around:"` — a direct positive claim instead of the "not X, not Y" AI cadence. While there, I folded a triple restatement of "she makes her own looks" into a single clause so the fashion paragraph advances instead of circling.

Everything else I left alone on purpose — the strongest lines (the R.I.P. cold open + obituary callback, "I set up that dinner and I invited Kanye," "She handed it over wet," "The muse builds the muse") and the emotional beats were doing their job, and over-editing would have flattened the voice.

**Verified mechanically** (not by feel): em-dashes are confined to comments and quote-attribution lines (lint: no prose em-dashes), no banned AI phrases.

